Light desserts
Is it possible to prepare a fine dessert bypassing the baking process? Easy if you get the gentle power of Philadelphia cream cheeses.

01 Nov 2019, 14:43

Philadelphia cream cheeses are just among the TOP 20 most popular cheeses in the world. The harmonious combination of creamy consistency and versatile taste has made them a true treasure trove of world cuisine.
Useful variety
Made with Philadelphia cream and cheese, they are presented with a wide variety of flavors today.
The manufacturer keeps his hand on the pulse of consumer demand and responds quickly to society's demands. For example, for people with lactose intolerance, the lactose-free version of cream cheese is released, and for fans of slimness, it is the lightweight version of Philadelphia, which includes less fat.
Philadelphia cream cheeses are just among the TOP 20 most popular cheeses in the world.
These delicious and wholesome cheese treats are a great solution for the right nutritionists, as they include balanced protein, essential amino acids and vitamins A, B1, B6, B12, C, PP and K.
Such cheeses are suitable for the preparation of a variety of dishes: cheesecakes and sushi, cream soups and salads, spicy sauces, desserts and fruit cocktails.
Enjoy the preparation of delicate desserts, experimenting with different ingredients and creating authoring recipes.


Philadelphia Cherry Dessert


Product: Philadelphia OriginalSupplies: 6. Cooking Time: 1 hour 20 minutes.


Photo: Philadelphia



Photo credit: Philadelphia Original

Ingredients:

2 packs of Philadelphia Original (175 g each);
100 g biscuit biscuits;
300 g yogurt with a fat content of 1.5%;
50 g butter;
1 bag of gelatin;
100 ml of water;
3 tsp. lemon juice;
50 g of powdered sugar;
1 tsp vanilla sugar;
125 ml of cherry jam;
1 sprig of fresh lemon balm.

Pour over 100 ml of cold boiled water and leave for one hour until ready. Meanwhile, grind the biscotti in a blender until smooth. Cook the melted butter, add it to the chopped cookies and mix thoroughly. Evenly spread the prepared mass into 6 glasses. Infusing gelatin, whisk the yogurt with a mixer or whisk. In a separate bowl, cook the cream by mixing Philadelphia Original cream cheese with lemon juice, icing sugar and vanilla sugar.
Put in a glass layer of cream and cherry jam. Put prepared portions in the refrigerator for 45 minutes. We take out glasses with dessert and decorate each serving with cherry berries and fresh lemon balm leaves.


Dessert "Fruit mix with oatmeal"


Product: Philadelphia Light Serving Quantity: 2. Cooking Time: 30 minutes.


Photo: Philadelphia Light



Photo: Philadelphia Light

Ingredients:

60 g Philadelphia Light;
2 tsp. nuts of your choice (pecans, peanuts, walnuts);
10th c. l. oat flakes for quick cooking;
80 ml of milk (1.5% fat);
1 apple;
300 g of mango or banana pulp;
130 ml of orange juice (can be replaced by your taste).

Grind nuts, mix with oat flour, orange juice and milk, put in a food container and refrigerate overnight. Cut 4 thin slices of apples to decorate the dessert. From the rest of the apples, mangoes or bananas, we make a smoothie. Put in glasses cooled oat mixture, fruit puree, Philadelphia Light cream cheese, decorate with sliced apples and serve.


Muesli with fruits and berries dessert


Product: Philadelphia Lactose-free Number of servings: 2. Cooking time: 10 minutes.


Photo: Philadelphia



Photo: Philadelphia lactose free

Ingredients:

75 g Philadelphia Cream Cheese Lactose free;
2 tbsp. l. milk;
60 g of muesli with nuts;
150 g of fresh fruits (berries) to choose from.

Divide a portion of Philadelphia Lactose free cream cheese into two dessert glasses. Cut the prepared fruit, leave the part for decoration. Mix granola with fruits (berries). Put this mixture into glasses. Decorate at will.


Chocolate Pleasure Dessert


Product: Philadelphia Milka Servings: 4. Cooking Time: 30 minutes.


Photo: Philadelphia Milka



Photo: Philadelphia Milka

Ingredients:

250 g Philadelphia Milka Cream Cheese;
1 tbsp. cherry juice with pulp (or to taste);
1 tsp cinnamon
3 tbsp. l. milk;
4 Milka Pieguski Cookies (or to taste).

Add the cinnamon juice and bring to a boil. Allow to cool for 10 minutes and distribute over glasses. Mix Philadelphia Milka with milk and put in glasses. Decorate the pieces with cookies on top. Cool before serving.
